result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Michael D Welch was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Defendant Michael D Welch in court with Attorney William M Ginsberg.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case called for plea and sentence hearing.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1. Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed by operation of law.  State makes sentencing recommendations.  Kevin S sworn-in and testified.  Kathleen K. sworn-in and testified.   Attorney Ginsberg makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - __ days)
  -  18 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  18 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

*D/L REVOCATION: 36 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 
*Attend Victim Impact Panel on 6/25/14

BLOOD WARRANT FEE:  $10.00 (to be paid to Waukesha County District Attorney's Office)
